President Joe Biden visited Pittsburgh to talk about the importance of investing in infrastructure and manufacturing in order to build a better America. He highlighted the recent collapse of a bridge in Pittsburgh and emphasized the need to repair and upgrade the country's aging infrastructure. Biden mentioned the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, which includes the largest investment in bridges since the Eisenhower era. He also discussed the importance of manufacturing in America and mentioned several companies that have made investments in the country, such as Intel and General Motors. Biden emphasized the need to invest in research and development, reduce the cost of childcare and insulin, and create jobs in clean energy. He also spoke about the impact of extreme weather events and the importance of investing in resilience. Finally, Biden discussed the Build Back Better plan and how it will help working families and address the challenges faced by the country.